<p>
<seg id=1> Millions of people all over Russia held demonstrations against President Yeltsin on Wednesday, and they demanded the government to pay for their deferred salaries. </seg>
<seg id=2> However, the actual figure of the demonstrators was much smaller than forty million, which is the figure expected by the organizers. </seg>
<seg id=3> An insignificant number of demonstrators gathered outside the Kremlin in Moscow, and many of them waved the communist banners. </seg>
<seg id=4> The would-be president Lebed addressed a speech to the masses that gathered for a meeting in the Siberian city Klasnoyask. </seg>
<seg id=5> He indicated that the investors in Russia and Western countries were losing their patience in waiting for the real economic reform. </seg>
</p>
